---
title: Azure DevOps
description: Azure DevOps Widget Configuration
layout: ../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro
---
This widget have 2 functions:
1. Pipelines - This type checks if the relevant pipeline is running or not, and if not, on which status it end.\
Allowed fields: `["result", "status", "buildId"]`.

2. Pull Requests - This type gives back the amount of open PRs, the amount of the PRs you have open, and how many PRs that you open are marked 
as 'Approved' by atleast 1 person and not yet completed.\
Allowed fields: `["totalPrs", "myPrs", "approvedNotCompleted"]`.


You will need to generate an API token for an existing user. To do so follow these steps:

1. Navigate to azure organization portal. (https://dev.azure.com/{organization})
2. Click user settings. (top corner next to your name badge.)
3. Click Personal-access-token.
4. Create new token with `Build` -> `Read` permissions.
5. Put PAT in widget.key settings.



```yaml
widget:
    type: azureDevOps
    azureType: Piplines / PullRequests
    organization: my-organization
    project: my-project
    userEmail: my-organization-email (Pull Requests)
    repositoryId: my-repository-id (name) (Pull Requests)
    definitionId: pipeline definition id (Pipelines)
    branchName: fill-for-specific, leave-empty-for all. (Pipelines)
    key: personal-access-token
```
